# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Modernized recreation of the MSU/CAVS tutorials by Mark A. Tschopp
# Tutorial 5: uniaxial deformation of single-crystal aluminum.
#
# Loading mode is set by the index variable "mode": "tension" (default) or
# "compress"; set it in the LAMMPS-GUI "Set Variables" dialog or with
#   lmp -in deform.lmp -var mode compress
variable mode    index tension
variable temp    index 300.0     # temperature in K (try 10 for clearer defect images)
variable nequil  index 20000     # equilibration steps (20 ps)
variable ndeform index 20000     # deformation steps (-> strain 0.2)

# 1) Initialization
units metal
dimension 3
boundary p p p
atom_style atomic

# 2) System definition: <100>-oriented fcc Al, 10x10x10 cells (4000 atoms)
variable a0 equal 4.05
lattice fcc ${a0} orient x 1 0 0 orient y 0 1 0 orient z 0 0 1 origin 0.25 0.25 0.25
lattice fcc 4.05 orient x 1 0 0 orient y 0 1 0 orient z 0 0 1 origin 0.25 0.25 0.25
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 4.05 4.05 4.05
region box block 0 10 0 10 0 10
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (40.5 40.5 40.5)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 4000 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (40.5 40.5 40.5)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.001 seconds

# 3) Settings
pair_style eam/alloy
pair_coeff * * Al_zhou.eam.alloy Al
Reading eam/alloy potential file Al_zhou.eam.alloy with DATE: 2007-10-12

compute csym all centro/atom fcc
compute pea  all pe/atom

# 4) Equilibration at the target temperature and zero pressure (isotropic NPT)
timestep 0.001
velocity all create ${temp} 12345 mom yes rot no
velocity all create 300.0 12345 mom yes rot no
fix equi all npt temp ${temp} ${temp} 0.1 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
fix equi all npt temp 300.0 ${temp} 0.1 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
fix equi all npt temp 300.0 300.0 0.1 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
thermo 1000
thermo_style custom step temp pe lx ly lz press
run ${nequil}
run 20000
